<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>The real type refers to a number with decimal point, e.g. 1.2 or -29.8.</db:para>
<db:para>Example:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="qml">Item { width: 100.45; height: 150.82 }
</db:programlisting>
<db:para><db:emphasis role="bold">Note:</db:emphasis> In QML all reals are stored in double precision, <db:link xlink:href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEEE_754">IEEE floating point</db:link> format.</db:para>
<db:para>This basic type is provided by the QML language.</db:para>
